          // The Law & Order Formula Section
          section#law-order-formula.mb-5
            h2.h3.text-primary.mb-4
              i.bi.bi-tv-fill.me-2
              | The Law & Order Formula
            p.lead
              | Dick Wolf's "Law & Order" franchise has captivated audiences for decades,
              | thanks to a meticulously crafted formula that combines compelling storytelling with a consistent structure.
              | The key elements contributing to its enduring success include:

            .accordion#formulaAccordion.mb-4
              .accordion-item
                h3.accordion-header#headingBifurcated
                  button.accordion-button.collapsed(
                    type='button'
                    data-bs-toggle='collapse'
                    data-bs-target='#collapseBifurcated'
                    aria-expanded='false'
                    aria-controls='collapseBifurcated'
                  )
                    i.bi.bi-diagram-2.me-2
                    | 1. Bifurcated Structure
                .accordion-collapse.collapse#collapseBifurcated(
                  aria-labelledby='headingBifurcated'
                  data-bs-parent='#formulaAccordion'
                )
                  .accordion-body
                    p Each episode is divided into two distinct halves:
                    ul
                      li
                        strong Investigation:
                        |  The first half follows detectives as they investigate a crime, gather evidence, and apprehend suspects.
                      li
                        strong Prosecution:
                        |  The second half shifts focus to the legal proceedings, showcasing the district attorney's efforts to prosecute the accused.
                    p.
                      This dual approach offers viewers a comprehensive view of the criminal justice process, from the crime scene to the courtroom.

              .accordion-item
                h3.accordion-header#headingHeadlines
                  button.accordion-button.collapsed(
                    type='button'
                    data-bs-toggle='collapse'
                    data-bs-target='#collapseHeadlines'
                    aria-expanded='false'
                    aria-controls='collapseHeadlines'
                  )
                    i.bi.bi-newspaper.me-2
                    | 2. "Ripped from the Headlines" Storytelling
                .accordion-collapse.collapse#collapseHeadlines(
                  aria-labelledby='headingHeadlines'
                  data-bs-parent='#formulaAccordion'
                )
                  .accordion-body
                    p.
                      "Law & Order" often draws inspiration from real-life events, adapting contemporary news stories into its narrative.
                      This technique adds a layer of authenticity and relevance, engaging viewers with familiar issues and ethical dilemmas.

              .accordion-item
                h3.accordion-header#headingStructure
                  button.accordion-button.collapsed(
                    type='button'
                    data-bs-toggle='collapse'
                    data-bs-target='#collapseStructure'
                    aria-expanded='false'
                    aria-controls='collapseStructure'
                  )
                    i.bi.bi-list-ol.me-2
                    | 3. Consistent Episode Structure
                .accordion-collapse.collapse#collapseStructure(
                  aria-labelledby='headingStructure'
                  data-bs-parent='#formulaAccordion'
                )
                  .accordion-body
                    p The series adheres to a reliable format, typically featuring:
                    ol
                      li
                        strong Teaser:
                        |  Introduction of the crime.
                      li
                        strong Investigation:
                        |  Detectives gather evidence and identify suspects.
                      li
                        strong Arrest:
                        |  Culmination of the investigation leading to an arrest.
                      li
                        strong Trial Preparation:
                        |  Prosecutors build their case.
                      li
                        strong Trial:
                        |  Courtroom proceedings and verdict.
                    p This structure provides a familiar rhythm that keeps audiences engaged.

              .accordion-item
